  "domain_summary": "The productized-services domain reveals significant pain points with freelance developers including ghosting, communication breakdowns, and quality control issues, while established productized landing page services offer structured alternatives. Major freelance platforms (Upwork, Toptal, Fiverr) publish vetting metrics but hide project completion/abandonment rates, creating a transparency gap. Only limited productized landing page services exist with transparent operations, with SprintPage being the sole service offering fixed 48-hour turnaround and published workflows. The market shows a potential shift from freelance to vetted/productized services, though verification data is limited.",
